column2: #read in saved data
safely_managed_raw_df <- read_csv(file=paste(raw_dir, '1.5_DUIO/Safely_Managed_Water_data.csv', sep="/"))
#score the data
#function to calculate 10 year window
window_fun <- function(date_start, date_end) {
temp <- safely_managed_raw_df %>%
filter(between(year,date_start,date_end) ) %>%
group_by(iso3c, geo) %>%
mutate(max_value=max(data_value, na.rm=T),
max_value=if_else(max_value!=-Inf,max_value,-99)
mutate(data_quality=if_else((max_value>=99.5),1,as.numeric(data_quality))) %>% #because JMP imputes values indefinitely forward if value for water reaches >99.5%
summarise(data_quality=mean(data_quality, na.rm=T)) %>% #average over 10 years
pivot_wider(
names_from = 'geo',
values_from = 'data_quality'
mutate(
SPI.D1.5.SAFE.MAN.WATER=case_when(
(Rural>=0.5 & Urban>=0.5) ~ 1, #urban rural breakdown gets 1 point
(Rural>=0.5 | Urban>=0.5 | National>=0.5) ~ 0.5, #partial data at at least one geography gets 0.5
TRUE ~ 0
select(iso3c, SPI.D1.5.SAFE.MAN.WATER) %>%
mutate(date=date_end)
# 10 Year window
#create this database for each year from 2004 to 2019 using a 10 year window
start=i-9
end=i
temp_df <- window_fun(start,end)
assign(paste('safe_managed_',end, sep=""), temp_df)
